Anh - Anh
butterfingers
■ noun (plural same) informal a clumsy person, especially one who fails to hold a catch.
Derivatives
butterfingeredadjective

sentences.en: He's a real butterfingers and keeps spilling dishes when he brings an order to the table.
sentences.vi: Anh ấy rất vụng về và thường đánh rơi các đĩa thức ăn khi anh ấy mang thức ăn đến bàn.

sentences.en: My brother is a bull in a China shop, a butterfingers.
sentences.vi: Anh tôi là người vụng về, hậu đậu.

sentences.en: Pete's a hard worker. But he has a tough time holding a restaurant job. He's a real Butterfingers and keeps spilling dishes when he brings an order to the table.
